The paper discusses data structures for storing and querying sets of k-mers, which are commonly used in biological sequencing data analysis. This topic falls under the intersection of computer science and biology, and thus could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on data structures for efficient storage and retrieval of k-mer sets. 

cs.DB (Databases) is also likely, as the paper discusses methods for querying large datasets of DNA sequences. 

cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility, as the paper discusses computational methods for analyzing biological data. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possibility, as machine learning techniques are often used in biological data analysis. 

cs.BIO (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) is also a likely category, as the paper specifically discusses the use of k-mers in biological sequencing data analysis.
